div.div: Plotting Complex Functions in Matplotlib (Python) from a slider?

If we used the example you put of f(xj) = (a)(b)(xj)^c; j = sqrt(-1) and assuming that the x-axis will be the domain values (xj) then it is possible to use this code to plot both of the real value and complex one with this code #matplotlib.pyplot for the graph import matplotlib.pyplot as plt (14 more lines were trimmed) then for the slider, we can add slider widget from matplotlib.widget (find more info about it in the documentation), so we can use this code #import matplotlib.pyplot for the graph import matplotlib.pyplot as plt (47 more lines were trimmed) However, it is more efficient to use other graphs, as a 3D graph with the xj as a domain and the complex numbers with real and imaginary values in the y and z axes as a range.
How to plot a complex-valued function of a real variable in python with matplotlib

To plot a complex-valued function of a real variable you have to specify that the range of the function is complex numbers so that NumPy arrays are able to store complex numbers. You can do this by adding +0j to the function's variable, so the code will be like this #matplotlib.pyplot for the graph import matplotlib.pyplot as plt (18 more lines were trimmed)
Next js on Hostinger VPS does not connect to correct Express js backend

I am running two instances on the VPS. One serving the frontend, other the backend. The front is a React application with Next js. The back is an Express js server. The front fetches some data from the back in the following code: fetch('http://localhost:8080/api/login', { method: 'POST', (20 more lines were trimmed) However, it connects to my local machine express js server instead of the VPS one. When the server on my machine is disabled, no data is fetched. I am sure that the server on the VPS is working since I can access it from my machine. I am using Hostinger with CloudPanel. I have set up the website using Cloud Panel as a node js application on port 3000. The front is served successfully, the only issue is with communication channel.
